9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 692, L.D. 1063, “An Act to Require
10 Competitive Procurement of Electricity from Generators Fueled by Municipal Solid Waste
11 in Conjunction with Recycling”
12 Amend the bill by inserting before section 1 the following:
13 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3210, sub-§3, ¶A, as amended by PL 2023, c. 361, §1, is
14 further amended to read:
15 A. For the purposes of meeting the portfolio requirement under this subsection, a 300%
16 multiplier is applied to the output of a generator fueled by municipal solid waste in
17 conjunction with recycling that has obtained a solid waste facility license from the
18 Department of Environmental Protection.
19 This paragraph is repealed January 1, 2027 2026.'
20 Amend the bill in section 1 in §3210-K in subsection 1 in the 6th and 7th lines (page
21 1, lines 10 and 11 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "pays state excise, income,
22 property and sales taxes" and inserting the following: 'is licensed by the Department of
23 Environmental Protection as a solid waste facility in accordance with Title 38, section
24 1310-N'
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment changes the repeal date applicable to the law that applies a 300%
2299 multiplier to the output of a generator fueled by municipal solid waste in conjunction with
3300 recycling for the purposes of the Class II resource portfolio requirements. The amendment
3311 also requires that a generator fueled by municipal solid waste in conjunction with recycling
3322 that may be selected for a contract for energy and renewable energy credits in accordance
3333 with the bill must be licensed in accordance with the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 38,
3344 section 1310-N, which provides that a license from the Department of Environmental
